<br>
DPS/MPS Ratio Explained: Instead of a straight Damage/Mana Ratio we have gone one step further to take the Damage/Mana Ratio to be divided by the total cast time. <br>
The total cast time is the casting time + recast time + duration of a spell. In other words the total time to cast a spell and be able to recast it after it has completed its maximum damage.<br>
<br>
This new ratio of DPS/MPS (Damage Per Second by Mana Per Second Ratio) allows us to see exactly how a spells efficiency (both in terms of damage and mana use) are affected by AA or Focus Items. The higher the number indicates the higher amount of damage done per mana spent per second and consequently means it is more efficient than a lower number.<br>
 <br>
<br>
I dont understand exactly SoS has a higher Damage/Mana ratio and Higher DPS.... how could DoT have higher DamageoverTime/ManaoverTime ratio.... did they calculate something wrong? Everything seems right. Boy that sure in intuitivly seeming wrong but i guess its right...... <br>
<br>
Lets see SoS has a higher DPS so SoS does 10K damage faster than DoT. SoS has a higher Damage per Mana ratio so it does 10K damage with less total mana. How can it be worse over time when it does 10K damage faster with less mana????? <br>
<br>
